      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky start to the program. HELLUVA KISS (4) had the drop on the leaders then let down nicely but couldn't match Lipstick on debut over 1100m at Wyong last start. Sure to appreciate the extra trip and looks the testing material. SPICE PRAWN (8) resumed with a modest fourth behind tearaway winner Journeyman over this distance at Warwick Farm last time out. Hasn't seen a dry track for a long while - a firmer deck here and the winkers going on should spark some improvement. BUBBLES UP (2) is a first starter by Churchill from a Danehill Dancer mare who has produced five winners from six foals including Home Ground at stakes level. A nice trial here recently suggests she has some talent. SPHERE (7) was just a pass mark at Gosford last time. McDonald takes over in a last attempt to get something out of this prep. Recent Warwick Farm trial winner OURAGAN (6) is a debutante who looks ready to run well for the Cave stable.",
